  <h1 class="gem-c-title__text ">
    Our energy use
  </h1>
</div>

    </div>
    
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      
  <p class="gem-c-lead-paragraph ">
    The Department for Transport's measures to reduce energy consumption and costs, and carbon emissions
  </p>

      
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-row ">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
        <div id="contents" class="app-c-contents-list-with-body">
    
        <div class="responsive-bottom-margin">
          
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>The Department publishes, in real-time, the <a rel="external" href="http://webview2.ecodriver.net/dft/">energy used in its headquarters building</a>. We also make our <a rel="external" href="http://data.gov.uk/dataset/dft-energy-use" title="DFT energy use data">energy use data</a> available in a format that can be reused.</p>

<h3 id="more-efficient-building">More efficient building</h3>

<p>To make our headquarters in London more efficient, we:</p>

<ul>
  <li>are installing more energy-efficient lighting</li>
  <li>have installed pulse meters on our electric and gas meters so we can identify and fix wastage</li>
  <li>have switched off all unnecessary lighting in reception areas</li>
  <li>have installed timers on all hot water heaters in tea-points so that theyâ€™re not on in the evenings or at weekends</li>
  <li>have switched off and isolated all heaters in stairwells</li>
</ul>

<p>We are currently assessing the CO2 benefits of the above measures.</p>

